Title : Arthur Smith (curator)
Text : '''Arthur Hamilton Smith''' (1860–1941) was a British museum curator and archaeologist.

His brothers were civil servant [[Henry Babington Smith]] and MP [[James Parker Smith]].  All three attended [[Trinity College, Cambridge]] and were members of the [[Cambridge Apostles]].<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Sy8Ym9N3tgUC&pg=PA36&lpg=PA36 |title=The Cambridge Apostles, 1820-1914 |last=Lubenow |first=W.C. |authorlink = W. C. Lubenow|pages=36, 256 |publisher=[[Cambridge University Press]] |isbn=9780521572132 |date=29 October 1998 |access-date=23 August 2016 |via=Google Books}}</ref>

Smith was Keeper of Greek and Roman Antiquities at the [[British Museum]] from 1909 to 1925. In addition, he served as President of the [[Society for the Promotion of Hellenic Studies]] from 1924 to 1929 and Director of the [[British School at Rome]] from 1928 to 1930 and in 1932.<ref name="Oxford DNB">{{cite ODNB|last=Cook|first=B. F.|title=Smith, Arthur Hamilton (1860–1941)|id=36128}}</ref>

